<paragraph blockId="45.[188,1399,1889,2021]" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" box="[189,265,1889,1914]" class="Polychaeta" family="Nereididae" genus="Nereis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Phyllodocida" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" phylum="Annelida" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[189,265,1889,1914]" italics="true" pageId="45" pageNumber="46">Nereis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with dorsal brownish pigmentation as trapezoidal transverse bands; parapodial glands dark. Jaws with 6 denticles; paragnaths formula: I: 
<quantity box="[658,703,1924,1950]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.08" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" unit="in" value="2.0">2 in</quantity>
tandem; II: about 
<quantity box="[920,980,1924,1950]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="7.112" pageId="45" pageNumber="46" unit="in" value="28.0">28 in</quantity>
three rows; III: about 50; IV: about 34; V: 0; VI: 3–5; VII–VIII: 2 irregular bands with about 60 paragnaths (largest paragnaths in I, VI, VII–VIII).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
